<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861222-0064 </DOCNO><HL> Mayflower Buyout Completed</HL><DD> 12/22/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> MFLTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)TRANSPORTATION, TRUCK AND SHIP LINES, RAILROADS (TRA) </IN><DATELINE> INDIANAPOLIS  </DATELINE><TEXT>   MG Holdings Inc. said its MG Acquiring Corp. unit completed its $260 million leveraged buyout of Mayflower Group Inc.    The MG concerns were formed to acquire Mayflower. As reported earlier, a management-led investor group announced plans in October to take the trucking concern private for $31.50 a share. In a leveraged buyout, a company is acquired in a transaction financed mostly by debt, which ultimately is paid from the target company's operations or by sales of its assets. </TEXT></DOC>